               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Tarikh i Banakati. Full title: Raudat uli'l-albab fi tawarikh al-akabir wa-'l-ansab by Banākatī, Dāvūd ibn Muḥammad, d. 1329 or 30
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="CODRINGTON.READE_NO_26_BOX_14-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/147349766/" key="person_147349766">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Banākatī, Dāvūd ibn Muḥammad, d. 1329 or 30</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">داود بن محمد فخر الدين بناكتى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9618">Tarikh i Banakati. Full title: Raudat uli'l-albab fi tawarikh al-akabir wa-'l-ansab.</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_9618">Vol. 1. containing the first six and part of the seventh book.</title>
                     <note>Second flyleaf, recto: Presented to the Oriental Translation Commit[tee] by Sir A Malet Bart. Folio 1a. Title and a verse indicating ownership in Persian beside a rectangular seal, illegible here but repeated by the same verse on the final folio, verso, of Fadl 'Ali al-Husaini, dated 118 (for 1108?). Final folio, verso. Two futher impressions, largely effaced of a round seal dated 984. Upside down inside front (originally back) cover: armorial bookplate of Sir Cha. Warre Malet. A general History up to A.H. 717.(A.D. 1317). Uniform with Codrington/Reade No 27, which contains the rest of the work. Headings in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Hamd i bi hadd u sipas i bi qiyas sazayi padshahi tawanad bud (Differs from Ethe's incipit)</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp. 79-80.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, i, pp. 79-80.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No 18.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For Sir Alexander Malet's gift see the Transactions, 1830, pp. xxxiv-xxxv.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
